I like how you illustrate in a clear way something that is unintuitive for people coming from a more traditional class-based background; the scoping of <i>this</i>.<p>It's easy to see how it applies locally to descendants of the original object, such as here:<p><pre><code>  var person = Object.create(null);
  defineProperty(person, 'fullName', function() {
    return this.firstName + ' ' + this.lastName;
  });
</code></pre>
where neither <i>fullname</i> nor <i>person</i> even have those properties, but their descendents do.
